The paper discusses the development of the SP machine, which is based on the SP theory of intelligence and its realisation in the SP computer model. The SP theory of intelligence is a general theory of cognition that has applications in several areas of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper discusses the potential applications of the SP machine in several of these areas, which suggests that it could be relevant to all of these sub-categories. However, given the emphasis on unsupervised learning and pattern recognition, as well as the mention of speech and visual images, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories in that order.
